18
00:01:15.601 --> 00:01:17.655
<i>All modern electronics
were fried.</i>

19
00:01:17.738 --> 00:01:19.096
(GLASS SHATTERING)

20
00:01:19.179 --> 00:01:21.245
<i>Most things didn't work anymore.</i>

21
00:01:22.479 --> 00:01:24.398
<i>People thought the governments
would take charge</i>

22
00:01:24.481 --> 00:01:25.498
<i>and fix things.</i>

23
00:01:25.581 --> 00:01:27.680
(SCOFFS) <i>Wishful thinking.</i>

24
00:01:29.090 --> 00:01:32.274
<i>Warlords seized control
of local governments</i>

25
00:01:32.357 --> 00:01:34.423
<i>and ruled large parts of Europe.</i>

26
00:01:36.493 --> 00:01:38.427
(RIOTERS CLAMORING)

27
00:01:40.266 --> 00:01:42.332
<i>They thought everything
was gonna be fine.</i>

28
00:01:43.599 --> 00:01:45.434
<i>I knew better. of course.</i>

29
00:01:47.603 --> 00:01:50.259
<i>Starving cities
turned into graveyards.</i>

30
00:01:50.342 --> 00:01:51.623
<i>Money was useless.</i>

31
00:01:51.706 --> 00:01:54.065
<i>medicine and fuel
nowhere to be found</i>

32
00:01:54.148 --> 00:01:55.708
<i>and diseases spread.</i>

33
00:01:57.382 --> 00:01:59.580
<i>I guess I was better equipped
for this.</i>

34
00:02:00.451 --> 00:02:02.601
<i>I was a survivor.</i>

35
00:02:02.684 --> 00:02:04.783
<i>And I was soon doing
what I always did.</i>

36
00:02:05.456 --> 00:02:06.785
