254
00:17:43.096 --> 00:17:45.576
We're busting our asses
every day

255
00:17:45.659 --> 00:17:47.578
to rebuild this thing
from the ground up.

256
00:17:47.661 --> 00:17:49.547
despite the efforts of people
trying to stop us.

257
00:17:49.630 --> 00:17:50.794
like General Volkov.

258
00:17:52.105 --> 00:17:53.683
Right. the guy
who wouldn't know culture

259
00:17:53.766 --> 00:17:55.586
if it smacked him in the face.

260
00:17:55.669 --> 00:17:57.405
He's an agent of chaos.

261
00:17:58.573 --> 00:18:00.804
He'd rather see the world burn
and rule the ashes.

262
00:18:02.214 --> 00:18:03.594
And you see yourself
differently?

263
00:18:03.677 --> 00:18:07.499
(CHUCKLES) Cynicism?

264
00:18:07.582 --> 00:18:10.007
Believe me
when I tell you. Jake.

265
00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:12.735
this is not a job I wanted.

266
00:18:12.818 --> 00:18:15.177
When the solar flare hit.
we lost our humanity.

267
00:18:15.260 --> 00:18:17.377
You saw what people did
in the dark.

268
00:18:17.460 --> 00:18:19.610
No one anticipated
the world would burn

269
00:18:19.693 --> 00:18:21.231
as quickly as it did.

270
00:18:23.235 --> 00:18:24.366
People panicked.

271
00:18:25.336 --> 00:18:26.764
Some became barbarians.

272
00:18:28.141 --> 00:18:29.686
Lucky you.

273
00:18:29.769 --> 00:18:31.358
Those ivory towers
that you're building

274
00:18:31.441 --> 00:18:33.162
will keep the barbarians at bay.

275
00:18:33.245 --> 00:18:34.328
And you'll all be safe.

276
00:18:34.411 --> 00:18:37.694
Well. everyone's not as
resourceful as you are. Jake.

277
00:18:37.777 --> 00:18:39.630
They don't have
your skills or grit

278
00:18:39.713 --> 00:18:42.138
to survive in this new world.

279
00:18:42.221 --> 00:18:43.682
They need protection.

280
00:18:44.388 --> 00:18:45.636
Without these walls.

281
00:18:45.719 --> 00:18:48.078
more and more
would have been slaughtered.

282
00:18:48.161 --> 00:18:49.277
What about the ones
outside the wall?

283
00:18:49.360 --> 00:18:51.510
What about the ones hiding?
You gonna let them in too?

284
00:18:51.593 --> 00:18:52.790
All are welcome. Jake.

285
00:18:54.299 --> 00:18:55.694
Even you.

286
00:19:03.407 --> 00:19:05.737
Minister Fuentes tells me
you are reluctant

287
00:19:06.740 --> 00:19:07.823
to cross the Channel.

288
00:19:07.906 --> 00:19:11.299
No. I'm not reluctant. I'm...
I'm dead set against it.

289
00:19:11.382 --> 00:19:13.730
Maybe that's because you
haven't seen the big picture.

290
00:19:13.813 --> 00:19:15.798
(UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING)

291
00:19:15.881 --> 00:19:17.338
I don't wanna see
the big picture.

292
00:19:17.421 --> 00:19:20.110
The big picture is ugly
and cruel.

293
00:19:20.193 --> 00:19:21.324
No.

294
00:19:22.294 --> 00:19:23.443
Not all of it.

295
00:19:23.526 --> 00:19:26.248
We are spending a lot of time

296
00:19:26.331 --> 00:19:28.661
restoring her
to her original beauty.

297
00:19:29.763 --> 00:19:31.664
You'll be a free man. Jake.

298
00:19:32.865 --> 00:19:34.667
Unencumbered.

299
00:19:36.209 --> 00:19:38.128
Answerable to no man.

300
00:19:38.211 --> 00:19:40.196
And all I need is the wind.

301
00:19:40.279 --> 00:19:42.132
To fly away
and leave the bullshit behind.

302
00:19:42.215 --> 00:19:43.445
AUGUST: Hmm.

303
00:19:45.845 --> 00:19:48.831
The people and I want
our world back. Jake.

304
00:19:48.914 --> 00:19:51.339
And what would I be hunting
down for you this time?

305
00:19:51.422 --> 00:19:52.784
(AUGUST EXHALES)

306
00:19:54.227 --> 00:19:55.523
Mona.

307
00:19:58.429 --> 00:19:59.512
The<i> Mona Lisa?</i>

308
00:19:59.595 --> 00:20:01.712
In all her motherfucking glory.

309
00:20:01.795 --> 00:20:03.384
(CHUCKLES)

310
00:20:03.467 --> 00:20:06.387
Hate to break the bad news
to you. Your Majesty.

311
00:20:06.470 --> 00:20:08.620
but Paris was one of
the first cities to burn down.

312
00:20:08.703 --> 00:20:10.934
For sure. For sure.

313
00:20:11.937 --> 00:20:14.296
But here's something
you may not know.

314
00:20:14.379 --> 00:20:16.826
It's that when the flare hit.
the French government

315
00:20:16.909 --> 00:20:19.169
evacuated all
its national treasures

316
00:20:19.252 --> 00:20:21.714
to a secret storage facility.

317
00:20:22.486 --> 00:20:24.735
Everything from fine art

318
00:20:24.818 --> 00:20:26.950
to the president's
porcelain throne.

319
00:20:30.263 --> 00:20:32.644
How am I supposed to get there?

320
00:20:32.727 --> 00:20:35.398
The King's plane
flown by the King's pilot.

321
00:20:37.831 --> 00:20:39.849
And I get the boat?

322
00:20:39.932 --> 00:20:42.654
All the resources
and food you need.

323
00:20:42.737 --> 00:20:44.755
Hell. I'll even
give you a title.

324
00:20:44.838 --> 00:20:45.854
(CHUCKLES)

325
00:20:45.937 --> 00:20:49.166
Okay. well. if Fuentes
is the Minister of Defense

326
00:20:49.249 --> 00:20:52.580
and. uh... and you're the King.

327
00:20:53.517 --> 00:20:54.747
what would you make me?

328
00:20:57.620 --> 00:20:59.902
Motherfucker of
Cultural Appropriation.

329
00:20:59.985 --> 00:21:02.260
(LAUGHS)

330
00:21:03.989 --> 00:21:05.857
-(JAKE GRUNTS)
-(GLASSES CLINK)

331
00:21:06.761 --> 00:21:07.859
(JAKE EXHALES)

332
00:21:15.770 --> 00:21:17.359
-(SIGHS)
-(DOG WHINES)

333
00:21:17.442 --> 00:21:19.442
Hey. buddy. Yeah.

334
00:21:21.611 --> 00:21:22.925
Yeah.

335
00:21:23.008 --> 00:21:25.532
I won't be long. buddy.
Be back before you know it.

336
00:21:25.615 --> 00:21:27.237
-(CAR APPROACHES)
-(DOG WHINES SOFTLY)

337
00:21:27.320 --> 00:21:29.320
(CAR DOOR OPENS. CLOSES)

338
00:21:37.891 --> 00:21:40.298
-How you doing?
-Fine. yeah.

339
00:21:40.696 --> 00:21:42.333
How are you?

340
00:21:43.303 --> 00:21:45.255
I think this is
a really bad idea.

341
00:21:45.338 --> 00:21:46.916
You always seem to
come out on top.

342
00:21:46.999 --> 00:21:48.291
Yeah. if I always
come out on top.

343
00:21:48.374 --> 00:21:50.506
then why am I headed to
the worst place on the planet?

344
00:21:53.577 --> 00:21:56.314
Um. I left plenty of food
and water for Smoke.

345
00:21:57.911 --> 00:21:59.599
Look. will you promise.
if I don't make it back.

346
00:21:59.682 --> 00:22:01.469
you'll take care of him?

347
00:22:01.552 --> 00:22:02.914
I don't have anyone else to ask.

348
00:22:04.786 --> 00:22:05.935
(EXHALES)

349
00:22:06.018 --> 00:22:08.590
I don't think Smoke
likes me very much.

350
00:22:09.890 --> 00:22:11.941
No. I'm not sure
if he trusts you.

351
00:22:12.024 --> 00:22:13.562
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

352
00:22:17.601 --> 00:22:19.469
Well. try not to die.

353
00:22:21.473 --> 00:22:23.491
Make sure I make it back.
(EXHALES)

354
00:22:23.574 --> 00:22:24.738
Always.

355
00:22:29.745 --> 00:22:31.844
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

356
00:22:33.617 --> 00:22:35.716
(ROUSING MUSIC PLAYING)

357
00:23:02.844 --> 00:23:04.334
JAKE: What?

358
00:23:04.417 --> 00:23:05.944
(GRUNTS)

359
00:23:13.855 --> 00:23:15.888
Takes your breath away.
don't she?

360
00:23:17.562 --> 00:23:19.826
Yeah. she's a right sort.
this one.

361
00:23:22.897 --> 00:23:24.717
We're flying in that?

362
00:23:24.800 --> 00:23:26.554
Huh? Yeah.

363
00:23:26.637 --> 00:23:29.491
-Is that safe?
-No. not technically.

364
00:23:29.574 --> 00:23:31.790
-It's got bullet holes in!
-Them?

365
00:23:31.873 --> 00:23:33.330
No. them's from last week.

366
00:23:33.413 --> 00:23:35.365
Little rendezvous with the boys.

367
00:23:35.448 --> 00:23:36.795
Oh.

368
00:23:36.878 --> 00:23:38.075
The King's waiting.

369
00:23:38.682 --> 00:23:40.616
Don't be late.

370
00:23:43.687 --> 00:23:46.068
AUGUST: We'll drop you in
under the cover of darkness.

371
00:23:46.151 --> 00:23:48.840
Now. your insertion point's
here.

372
00:23:48.923 --> 00:23:50.743
Outside this small village.

373
00:23:50.826 --> 00:23:53.944
Now. according to intel.
it's been cleared of rebels.

374
00:23:54.027 --> 00:23:55.847
Now. you'll hump it a little bit

375
00:23:55.930 --> 00:23:58.520
due north to Saint-Quentin.

376
00:23:58.603 --> 00:24:00.456
Now. that's a town
under occupation.

377
00:24:00.539 --> 00:24:02.572
So you got to go in quietly.

378
00:24:03.135 --> 00:24:04.086
Like a whisper.

379
00:24:04.169 --> 00:24:06.957
Like a baby fucking mouse.

380
00:24:07.040 --> 00:24:10.092
Now. make your way
to the city center.

381
00:24:10.175 --> 00:24:13.176
and our rebel liaison
will meet you there.

382
00:24:18.590 --> 00:24:19.853
City center.

383
00:24:21.626 --> 00:24:23.413
This is a big fucking area.

384
00:24:23.496 --> 00:24:24.843
How the hell
am I supposed to find them?

385
00:24:24.926 --> 00:24:26.383
Oh. don't worry about that.
they'll find you.

386
00:24:26.466 --> 00:24:29.617
Now. everything's hush-hush.
on the QT.

387
00:24:29.700 --> 00:24:31.487
Need-to-know basis.

388
00:24:31.570 --> 00:24:32.833
Yeah. I need to know.

389
00:24:34.738 --> 00:24:35.788
You need to know what?

390
00:24:35.871 --> 00:24:36.888
I need to know how the fuck

391
00:24:36.971 --> 00:24:38.725
-I'm getting out of there.
-Oh.

392
00:24:38.808 --> 00:24:40.430
The rebels will contact me

393
00:24:40.513 --> 00:24:42.663
when you've got hands on Mona.

394
00:24:42.746 --> 00:24:43.796
All right?

395
00:24:43.879 --> 00:24:46.799
And I'll drop the equipment
for an AirTEP evacuation

396
00:24:46.882 --> 00:24:48.669
three hours later.
(SNAPS FINGERS)

397
00:24:48.752 --> 00:24:51.441
-Three hours?
-You good?

398
00:24:51.524 --> 00:24:53.641
You know.
the plane's got holes in it.

399
00:24:53.724 --> 00:24:55.185
Never noticed.

400
00:24:56.188 --> 00:24:58.529
Wheels up. 10:00 p.m.

401
00:24:59.059 --> 00:25:00.091
My man.

402
00:25:06.539 --> 00:25:08.506
-(ENGINE IGNITION WHIRRS)
-Ready. Joe.

403
00:25:09.674 --> 00:25:11.542
(ENGINE SPLUTTERS. REVVING)

404
00:25:13.645 --> 00:25:15.271
Right. all set to go.

405
00:25:18.551 --> 00:25:20.470
JAKE: Uh...

406
00:25:20.553 --> 00:25:21.702
All the seat belts are broken.

407
00:25:21.785 --> 00:25:23.572
Ah. not worth the barney. mate.

408
00:25:23.655 --> 00:25:25.886
Strip of nylon's not gonna
help if she goes down. is it?

409
00:25:26.625 --> 00:25:28.610
All right? Here we go.

410
00:25:28.693 --> 00:25:29.710
(ENGINE REVS)

411
00:25:29.793 --> 00:25:31.859
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

412
00:25:57.821 --> 00:26:00.052
Ooh. what's up? What's that?

413
00:26:01.022 --> 00:26:03.253
(AIRPLANE RATTLES. JUDDERS)

414
00:26:06.566 --> 00:26:07.748
Oh. shit. Right.

415
00:26:07.831 --> 00:26:09.160
(BEEPING)

416
00:26:10.262 --> 00:26:11.851
-JAKE: Is everything okay?
-Yeah. yeah.

417
00:26:11.934 --> 00:26:14.755
Er. just doing some sums. Er...

418
00:26:14.838 --> 00:26:16.955
Yeah. I'm not sure
that gauge is working right.

419
00:26:17.038 --> 00:26:18.220
Er. I mean. it's either that

420
00:26:18.303 --> 00:26:20.596
or we're gonna run out of fuel
halfway there.

421
00:26:20.679 --> 00:26:23.225
So probably best to put on
your parachute just in case.

422
00:26:23.308 --> 00:26:24.978
Yeah.

423
00:26:27.587 --> 00:26:28.850
(GRUNTS)

424
00:26:35.991 --> 00:26:37.613
I pull this
to open the chute. right?

425
00:26:37.696 --> 00:26:40.011
Whoa. hold on.
You not done this before?

426
00:26:40.094 --> 00:26:41.848
-(FASTENER CLICKS)
-No.

427
00:26:41.931 --> 00:26:43.784
Oh. fucking amateur.

428
00:26:43.867 --> 00:26:46.688
Yes. that's the cord
that you pull.

429
00:26:46.771 --> 00:26:47.754
When do I pull it?

430
00:26:47.837 --> 00:26:50.333
I dunno. preferably
before you hit the ground.

431
00:26:51.743 --> 00:26:54.190
Relax. Have a kip or something.

432
00:26:54.273 --> 00:26:56.647
I'll take us the scenic route.
yeah?

433
00:26:58.651 --> 00:27:00.343
(PILOT GRUMBLES)

434
00:27:05.350 --> 00:27:07.317
PILOT: (CLEARS THROAT) Relax.

435
00:27:08.793 --> 00:27:10.892
(SERENE MUSIC PLAYING)

436
00:27:49.801 --> 00:27:50.784
(MUSIC SWELLS)

437
00:27:50.867 --> 00:27:52.622
-(AIRPLANE RATTLES)
-Fucking hell. here we go!

438
00:27:52.705 --> 00:27:55.086
We've got a rendezvous
with Volkov's boys.

439
00:27:55.169 --> 00:27:57.400
Come on. then!
Welcome to France. mate.

440
00:27:58.172 --> 00:27:59.908
(GUNFIRE)

441
00:28:01.780 --> 00:28:03.765
Right? Tell you what.
I'm gonna fly us through this.

442
00:28:03.848 --> 00:28:04.864
So gear up.

443
00:28:04.947 --> 00:28:06.768
Probably gonna have to drop
a little bit early.

444
00:28:06.851 --> 00:28:07.916
Got it.

445
00:28:09.249 --> 00:28:10.772
Five minutes
to bees and honey. mate.

446
00:28:10.855 --> 00:28:12.085
Let's make that money.

447
00:28:13.825 --> 00:28:16.206
Right. what I'm gonna
need you to do.

448
00:28:16.289 --> 00:28:18.208
I'm gonna fly us down
to 4.000 feet

449
00:28:18.291 --> 00:28:19.946
and you're gonna have to jump.
right?

450
00:28:20.029 --> 00:28:21.094
Got it.

451
00:28:23.164 --> 00:28:24.834
(GUNFIRE)

452
00:28:26.200 --> 00:28:28.101
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

453
00:28:28.807 --> 00:28:30.103
Good to go.

454
00:28:32.877 --> 00:28:34.224
Red cord. eh?

455
00:28:34.307 --> 00:28:36.813
-Deploy as soon as I open it?
-Yeah.

456
00:28:37.882 --> 00:28:39.717
Oh. I knew this was a bad idea.

457
00:28:41.446 --> 00:28:42.951
(AIR WHOOSHES)

458
00:28:43.987 --> 00:28:45.217
PILOT: Come on.

459
00:28:46.418 --> 00:28:48.238
-You've gotta go!
-(GRUNTS)

460
00:28:48.321 --> 00:28:49.991
(YELLS)

461
00:29:06.240 --> 00:29:08.306
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

462
00:29:10.013 --> 00:29:11.980
-(BODY THUDS)
-Oh. God!

463
00:29:26.799 --> 00:29:28.227
(EXHALES)

464
00:29:28.999 --> 00:29:30.801
(PANTING) Yeah.

465
00:29:31.430 --> 00:29:33.331
This is definitely a bad idea.

466
00:29:40.945 --> 00:29:42.780
(DOG HOWLS IN DISTANCE)

467
00:29:51.252 --> 00:29:53.285
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

468
00:30:17.509 --> 00:30:19.949
(ENGINE REVVING)

469
00:30:25.858 --> 00:30:27.073
(TURRET WHIRRING)

470
00:30:27.156 --> 00:30:28.859
MAN: Stay where you are!

471
00:30:31.160 --> 00:30:33.193
(PROJECTILE WHISTLES. EXPLODES)

472
00:30:34.229 --> 00:30:36.016
(REBELS SHOUTING)

473
00:30:36.099 --> 00:30:37.494
(WOMAN SHOUTS IN FRENCH)

474
00:30:39.498 --> 00:30:41.201
(MAN SHOUTING IN FRENCH)

475
00:30:47.176 --> 00:30:48.241
(GRENADE PIN CLICKS)

476
00:30:48.848 --> 00:30:50.426
(WOMAN IN FRENCH)

477
00:30:50.509 --> 00:30:52.377
WOMAN: (IN ENGLISH) Take cover!

478
00:30:55.448 --> 00:30:58.119
MAN: Goodbye and good luck.
They are waiting for you.

479
00:30:58.583 --> 00:31:00.550
Saint-Quentin is west!

480
00:31:06.360 --> 00:31:09.460
(CROWD CLAMORING AND SCREAMING)

481
00:31:11.904 --> 00:31:14.905
SOLDIER 1: Turn around and
show me your fucking head!

482
00:31:17.371 --> 00:31:18.909
(GUNSHOT)

483
00:31:20.143 --> 00:31:21.523
SOLDIER 1: Next.

484
00:31:21.606 --> 00:31:23.899
MAN: Sit the fuck down now.

485
00:31:23.982 --> 00:31:26.543
(SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING)

486
00:31:29.614 --> 00:31:32.923
A worthy opponent
is hard to find.

487
00:31:35.158 --> 00:31:37.994
This game taught me
so many things.

488
00:31:39.129 --> 00:31:41.180
But the most important lesson

489
00:31:41.263 --> 00:31:43.545
is to revere a strong adversary.

490
00:31:43.628 --> 00:31:46.284
-(GUNSHOTS)
-SOLDIER 2: On the ground!

491
00:31:46.367 --> 00:31:48.484
VOLKOV: You see.
I learned how to play

492
00:31:48.567 --> 00:31:50.321
when I was incarcerated.

493
00:31:50.404 --> 00:31:54.864
And prison. by design.
is a gladiatorial arena.

494
00:31:54.947 --> 00:31:59.246
One challenge after another.
a consistent power struggle.

495
00:32:00.645 --> 00:32:04.416
In the beginning.
it was terrifying.

496
00:32:06.057 --> 00:32:07.943
When I found chess.

497
00:32:08.026 --> 00:32:11.210
I discovered something
life changing.

498
00:32:11.293 --> 00:32:14.063
Playing against those
who were better than me

499
00:32:14.494 --> 00:32:16.329
made me better.

500
00:32:17.970 --> 00:32:20.956
I only saw improvement
when my skills were challenged

501
00:32:21.039 --> 00:32:24.667
and that's why
I demand from you...

502
00:32:26.110 --> 00:32:28.671
play your best.

503
00:32:31.049 --> 00:32:33.214
(UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING)

504
00:32:52.972 --> 00:32:55.434
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

505
00:33:00.144 --> 00:33:03.145
You don't even know
how to play. do you?

506
00:33:08.581 --> 00:33:10.350
(MAN SHRIEKS)

507
00:33:11.221 --> 00:33:12.385
Next.

508
00:33:17.161 --> 00:33:19.080
-Mmm.
-Volkov.

509
00:33:19.163 --> 00:33:22.017
One of our heavy guns fired
on the plane an hour ago.

510
00:33:22.100 --> 00:33:23.953
-What kind?
-Single prop.

511
00:33:24.036 --> 00:33:27.103
