(BREATHES HEAVILY)

1110
01:12:38.454 --> 01:12:40.850
(VENTILATION MACHINERY WHIRRING)

1111
01:12:52.094 --> 01:12:53.533
This'll have to do.

1112
01:13:00.971 --> 01:13:03.543
(ENGINE REVVING)

1113
01:13:16.426 --> 01:13:18.477
(STRAINING)

1114
01:13:18.560 --> 01:13:19.988
(ENGINE REVVING)

1115
01:13:29.065 --> 01:13:30.669
(ZIPPER UNFASTENS)

1116
01:14:26.496 --> 01:14:28.562
(SIGHS) It's a bad idea.

1117
01:14:30.126 --> 01:14:32.126
(PANTS)

1118
01:14:36.737 --> 01:14:38.506
(VENTILATION MACHINERY WHIRRING)

1119
01:14:47.946 --> 01:14:49.979
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1120
01:14:58.627 --> 01:15:00.139
(SIGHS) Shit.

1121
01:15:00.222 --> 01:15:02.629
(VENTILATION MACHINERY WHIRRING)

1122
01:15:05.997 --> 01:15:07.916
(WHIRRING)

1123
01:15:07.999 --> 01:15:09.064
(ROPE SNAPS)

1124
01:15:10.738 --> 01:15:12.903
-Oh. shit.
-(ROPE CREAKING)

1125
01:15:15.171 --> 01:15:16.122
(GUN CLICKS)

1126
01:15:16.205 --> 01:15:18.205
-(GUN CLICKING)
-Ah.<i> merde!</i>

1127
01:15:19.681 --> 01:15:21.681
(WHIRRING)

1128
01:15:23.652 --> 01:15:25.014
Ah. shit.

1129
01:15:26.886 --> 01:15:28.101
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

1130
01:15:28.184 --> 01:15:29.249
(GUN CLICKS)

1131
01:15:40.933 --> 01:15:42.570
(ROCKS CRUMBLING)

1132
01:15:46.543 --> 01:15:48.235
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1133
01:15:49.139 --> 01:15:51.073
(FAN BLADES STALLING)

1134
01:15:54.144 --> 01:15:57.112
(GRUNTS. STRAINS)

1135
01:16:01.283 --> 01:16:02.722
-(GRUNTS)
-(ROPE SNAPS)

1136
01:16:04.286 --> 01:16:06.154
-(HEAVY THUD)
-(GROANS)

1137
01:16:07.058 --> 01:16:08.662
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

1138
01:16:09.797 --> 01:16:10.715
(GRUNTS)

1139
01:16:10.798 --> 01:16:12.618
-(METAL CLANGS)
-Oh. shit.

1140
01:16:12.701 --> 01:16:14.081
It's flooded.

1141
01:16:14.164 --> 01:16:15.966
(WATER SLOSHING)

1142
01:16:19.070 --> 01:16:20.707
(ENGINE REVVING)

1143
01:16:29.619 --> 01:16:30.999
(SIGHS) Fuck you. August.

1144
01:16:31.082 --> 01:16:32.902
I knew this was a bad idea.

1145
01:16:32.985 --> 01:16:34.607
(WATER SPLASHING)

1146
01:16:34.690 --> 01:16:37.757
Minister of Cultural
Appropriation. my ass.

1147
01:16:38.320 --> 01:16:39.594
(INHALES DEEPLY)

1148
01:16:49.639 --> 01:16:52.200
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

1149
01:17:35.146 --> 01:17:37.212
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1150
01:17:50.359 --> 01:17:52.392
(GATE RATTLING)

1151
01:17:55.397 --> 01:17:57.397
(METAL CREAKING)

1152
01:18:01.843 --> 01:18:03.678
(GRUNTING)

1153
01:18:05.781 --> 01:18:07.766
-(GATE CLANGS)
-(GASPS)

1154
01:18:07.849 --> 01:18:10.718
(PANTING HEAVILY)

1155
01:18:21.390 --> 01:18:22.422
(GRUNTS)

1156
01:18:30.971 --> 01:18:32.036
Jake?

1157
01:18:32.808 --> 01:18:34.122
Jake!

1158
01:18:34.205 --> 01:18:36.843
-(METAL CLANGS)
-(EXHALES HEAVILY)

1159
01:18:37.879 --> 01:18:39.747
(PANTING)

1160
01:18:45.051 --> 01:18:47.183
(COUGHS. CLEARS THROAT)

1161
01:19:07.909 --> 01:19:09.256
Fucking knew it.

1162
01:19:09.339 --> 01:19:11.258
(GATE WHIRRING)

1163
01:19:11.341 --> 01:19:12.406
Jake!

1164
01:19:20.350 --> 01:19:21.448
Jake!

1165
01:19:22.352 --> 01:19:24.121
Are you okay? Jake!

1166
01:19:26.158 --> 01:19:28.125
JAKE: This is helping people?

1167
01:19:29.458 --> 01:19:31.179
DREA: (SIGHS)
I wanted to tell you

1168
01:19:31.262 --> 01:19:34.281
but August said
you wouldn't help if you knew.

1169
01:19:34.364 --> 01:19:36.001
You're goddamn right.

1170
01:19:38.170 --> 01:19:40.958
The U.S. made two atomic bombs
to drop on Japan.

1171
01:19:41.041 --> 01:19:42.289
Fat Man and Little Boy.

1172
01:19:42.372 --> 01:19:44.291
But there was a third.

1173
01:19:44.374 --> 01:19:46.865
set aside for Moscow.

1174
01:19:46.948 --> 01:19:49.817
in case the Red Army
didn't stop at Manchuria.

1175
01:19:50.512 --> 01:19:51.637
The Mona Lisa.

1176
01:19:51.720 --> 01:19:54.103
This bomb was meant to travel
a long way.

1177
01:19:54.186 --> 01:19:56.402
so there was
a safety measure added.

1178
01:19:56.485 --> 01:19:59.207
Without this plug inserted.
this bomb can't go off.

1179
01:19:59.290 --> 01:20:01.110
So August gets the bomb
and you get everything else?

1180
01:20:01.193 --> 01:20:03.277
August doesn't want this bomb
to use it.

1181
01:20:03.360 --> 01:20:05.213
He just wants to keep it away
from Volkov.

1182
01:20:05.296 --> 01:20:07.050
And you believe him?

1183
01:20:07.133 --> 01:20:08.986
(SCOFFS) What choice do I have?

1184
01:20:09.069 --> 01:20:10.757
You had a choice.

1185
01:20:10.840 --> 01:20:12.319
You could've kept me out of it.

1186
01:20:12.402 --> 01:20:13.958
But it would've been found.

1187
01:20:14.041 --> 01:20:15.388
And you know it. Jake.

1188
01:20:15.471 --> 01:20:16.763
I do trust August

1189
01:20:16.846 --> 01:20:18.996
just a little more
than I trust Volkov.

1190
01:20:19.079 --> 01:20:21.409
They're both a part
of the same hypocrisy.

1191
01:20:22.852 --> 01:20:24.181
I trusted you. Drea.

1192
01:20:25.855 --> 01:20:27.136
Look.

1193
01:20:27.219 --> 01:20:29.989
It might be too late for me
and the life I wanted.

1194
01:20:31.058 --> 01:20:33.322
But maybe. just maybe.

1195
01:20:34.226 --> 01:20:36.244
by stopping Volkov

1196
01:20:36.327 --> 01:20:39.082
someone else
can have that chance.

1197
01:20:39.165 --> 01:20:41.968
And how many have to die
while you're trying to stop him?

1198
01:20:45.567 --> 01:20:47.222
Jake. wait!

1199
01:20:47.305 --> 01:20:50.438
Come on. just...
just stay and fight with us.

1200
01:20:51.573 --> 01:20:53.426
Can't you see.
the Volkovs of this world.

1201
01:20:53.509 --> 01:20:56.869
they win
when good people do nothing?

1202
01:20:56.952 --> 01:20:58.413
They win anyway.

1203
01:21:00.252 --> 01:21:02.450
Jake! Jake!

1204
01:21:03.860 --> 01:21:04.892
Jake!

1205
01:21:10.592 --> 01:21:12.786
(REBELS SHOUTING)

1206
01:21:12.869 --> 01:21:14.902
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1207
01:21:17.566 --> 01:21:19.907
(JAKE GRUNTING)

1208
01:21:26.278 --> 01:21:27.574
(ENGINE STARTS)

1209
01:21:29.446 --> 01:21:31.380
(TIRES SCREECH)

1210
01:21:35.584 --> 01:21:37.617
(ENGINE REVVING)

1211
01:21:42.294 --> 01:21:44.261
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1212
01:22:04.613 --> 01:22:06.415
(MAP RUSTLING)

1213
01:22:07.418 --> 01:22:09.975
DREA: Okay. so look at this.

1214
01:22:10.058 --> 01:22:12.307
This road leads to Calais.

1215
01:22:12.390 --> 01:22:13.946
August has a team there.

1216
01:22:14.029 --> 01:22:15.310
And they'll be waiting
to transport

1217
01:22:15.393 --> 01:22:17.345
the Mona Lisa
across the Channel.

1218
01:22:17.428 --> 01:22:18.885
You got it?

1219
01:22:18.968 --> 01:22:21.661
Now this. keep it very safe.

1220
01:22:24.303 --> 01:22:25.500
Okay. good luck. guys.

1221
01:22:33.312 --> 01:22:35.114
Not your fight. Jake.

1222
01:22:36.348 --> 01:22:38.267
Not your fight.

1223
01:22:38.350 --> 01:22:40.335
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1224
01:22:40.418 --> 01:22:42.352
(FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING)

1225
01:22:44.224 --> 01:22:46.455
(MAN SHOUTS INSTRUCTIONS
INDISTINCTLY)

1226
01:22:58.469 --> 01:23:00.337
WOMAN: (SHOUTS) Volkov! Volkov!

1227
01:23:04.145 --> 01:23:05.591
-(MAN CRIES OUT)
-(GASPS)

1228
01:23:05.674 --> 01:23:07.641
(REBELS CLAMORING)

1229
01:23:19.391 --> 01:23:21.226
(REBELS GRUNT. YELL)

1230
01:23:41.347 --> 01:23:43.677
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1231
01:24:00.069 --> 01:24:01.530
And there she is.

1232
01:24:03.534 --> 01:24:04.698
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

1233
01:24:10.739 --> 01:24:13.311
SOLDIER:
General. the safety plug.

1234
01:24:21.189 --> 01:24:23.471
Isn't it funny?

1235
01:24:23.554 --> 01:24:27.079
They locked us up in cages
like the scum of the world

1236
01:24:27.162 --> 01:24:29.327
never to see the light again.

1237
01:24:30.330 --> 01:24:32.986
But then the light liberated us.

1238
01:24:33.069 --> 01:24:36.202
And now we rule their world.

1239
01:24:37.106 --> 01:24:38.717
We march to Calais.

1240
01:24:38.800 --> 01:24:40.800
The rest we take later.
Let's move!

1241
01:24:50.119 --> 01:24:51.349
SOLDIER: Advance!

1242
01:25:08.599 --> 01:25:10.023
(ENGINE SWITCHES OFF)

1243
01:25:10.106 --> 01:25:11.435
(SIGHS)

1244
01:25:13.670 --> 01:25:16.143
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

1245
01:25:23.581 --> 01:25:25.614
(RESOLUTE MUSIC PLAYING)

1246
01:25:53.611 --> 01:25:54.874
Drea?

1247
01:25:58.616 --> 01:25:59.666
Drea!

1248
01:25:59.749 --> 01:26:01.815
(FAINT COUGHING)

1249
01:26:06.558 --> 01:26:08.576
Hey. Hey. Drea.

1250
01:26:08.659 --> 01:26:10.560
Hey. Hey.

1251
01:26:11.398 --> 01:26:13.482
-Can you hear me?
-Yeah.

1252
01:26:13.565 --> 01:26:14.448
(GRUNTS)

1253
01:26:14.531 --> 01:26:17.534
Well. you were right.
It was pointless.

1254
01:26:18.669 --> 01:26:20.324
You shouldn't have come back.

1255
01:26:20.407 --> 01:26:22.260
(JAKE GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1256
01:26:22.343 --> 01:26:24.739
I'm sorry I lied to you.

1257
01:26:25.577 --> 01:26:27.232
Sorry I dragged you into this.

1258
01:26:27.315 --> 01:26:28.776
You didn't drag me
into anything.

1259
01:26:30.219 --> 01:26:31.830
You dragged me out.

1260
01:26:31.913 --> 01:26:34.371
But we got to get
that bomb back.

1261
01:26:34.454 --> 01:26:36.703
It's too late. Jake.

1262
01:26:36.786 --> 01:26:38.144
You said you could build a bomb

1263
01:26:38.227 --> 01:26:40.146
big enough to
blow up a tank. right?

1264
01:26:40.229 --> 01:26:42.610
-What about a train?
-Jake...

1265
01:26:42.693 --> 01:26:44.216
The train's headed
back to the city.

1266
01:26:44.299 --> 01:26:46.515
To get there
it's gotta cross the bridge.

1267
01:26:46.598 --> 01:26:48.286
All right. all I need to do
is get that plug

1268
01:26:48.369 --> 01:26:49.584
and make sure
the train doesn't stop.

1269
01:26:49.667 --> 01:26:51.586
You just gotta blow that bridge.

1270
01:26:51.669 --> 01:26:52.767
That's all?

1271
01:26:54.573 --> 01:26:55.722
Look... (SIGHS)

1272
01:26:55.805 --> 01:26:57.691
We can do this.

1273
01:26:57.774 --> 01:26:59.939
But if we're gonna do it.
we gotta do it now.

1274
01:27:00.711 --> 01:27:02.729
-Okay. you ready?
-Yeah.

1275
01:27:02.812 --> 01:27:04.302
Let's go. Come on.

1276
01:27:04.385 --> 01:27:05.945
Can you walk?

1277
01:27:06.816 --> 01:27:08.816
-Yeah.
-All right.

1278
01:27:10.721 --> 01:27:13.245
Get her fired up.
I'll be right back.

1279
01:27:13.328 --> 01:27:14.642
Okay.

1280
01:27:14.725 --> 01:27:16.725
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1281
01:27:42.819 --> 01:27:44.918
(ENGINE REVVING)

1282
01:27:46.493 --> 01:27:47.342
Go. go. go!

1283
01:27:47.425 --> 01:27:49.923
-(ENGINE REVVING)
-(TIRES SCREECHING)

1284
01:27:51.498 --> 01:27:52.860
What were you doing back there?

1285
01:27:54.369 --> 01:27:56.270
(EXPLOSIONS)

1286
01:28:10.418 --> 01:28:12.781
(ENGINE ACCELERATING)

1287
01:28:29.701 --> 01:28:31.224
Why are we going so slow?

1288
01:28:31.307 --> 01:28:33.688
It's dark with low visibility.
I have to take it slow.

1289
01:28:33.771 --> 01:28:35.624
Once we're on the straight
away past the bridge.

1290
01:28:35.707 --> 01:28:36.922
I'll be able
to pick up the pace.

1291
01:28:37.005 --> 01:28:38.561
He's not gonna like that.

1292
01:28:38.644 --> 01:28:40.365
I'm doing my best!

1293
01:28:40.448 --> 01:28:41.579
(MUTTERS) Asshole.

1294
01:28:46.047 --> 01:28:48.487
We are gonna have
a small window of opportunity.

1295
01:28:49.050 --> 01:28:50.606
I know.

1296
01:28:50.689 --> 01:28:52.476
-We gotta get ahead of 'em.
-Yeah.

1297
01:28:52.559 --> 01:28:54.053
(ENGINE REVVING)

1298
01:28:56.497 --> 01:28:57.595
There it is.

1299
01:29:00.468 --> 01:29:02.501
(TRAIN CHUGGING)

1300
01:29:11.611 --> 01:29:13.266
-Take a right at the fork.
-Okay.

1301
01:29:13.349 --> 01:29:14.513
Kill the lights.

1302
01:29:31.400 --> 01:29:32.747
So?

1303
01:29:32.830 --> 01:29:35.013
It is a concern
regarding visibility.

1304
01:29:35.096 --> 01:29:38.390
Oh. I don't remember giving
the order to be concerned.

1305
01:29:38.473 --> 01:29:39.489
You did not.

1306
01:29:39.572 --> 01:29:41.987
But the conductor assures me
he's doing his best.

1307
01:29:42.070 --> 01:29:44.627
His best. huh?

1308
01:29:44.710 --> 01:29:46.464
I think
he underestimates himself.

1309
01:29:46.547 --> 01:29:47.697
I think you're right.

1310
01:29:47.780 --> 01:29:50.798
I think he just needs some
help to fulfill his potential.

1311
01:29:50.881 --> 01:29:52.782
-Hmm.
-Just like you.

1312
01:29:54.555 --> 01:29:55.620
Checkmate.

1313
01:29:57.118 --> 01:29:58.623
Again.

1314
01:30:16.577 --> 01:30:17.627
(VOLKOV CLEARS THROAT)

1315
01:30:17.710 --> 01:30:21.367
I'm going slow because
we're carrying an atomic...

1316
01:30:21.450 --> 01:30:23.747
-(ENGINE ACCELERATING)
-That's your full potential.

1317
01:30:26.686 --> 01:30:27.934
Drop me at the overpass.

1318
01:30:28.017 --> 01:30:30.083
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1319
01:30:33.990 --> 01:30:35.693
JAKE: Get to that bridge.

1320
01:30:59.785 --> 01:31:00.601
So?

1321
01:31:00.684 --> 01:31:03.871
Some people just need
a little push.

1322
01:31:03.954 --> 01:31:05.954
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

1323
01:31:19.871 --> 01:31:21.739
(PIN CLATTERS)

1324
01:31:24.843 --> 01:31:26.205
(SOLDIER YELLS)

1325
01:31:27.879 --> 01:31:29.516
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

1326
01:31:50.902 --> 01:31:52.231
-(GRUNTS)
-(BLOW THUDS)

1327
01:31:58.679 --> 01:31:59.843
(SOLDIER GRUNTS)

1328
01:32:14.860 --> 01:32:16.189
(SOLDIER YELLS)

1329
01:32:27.136 --> 01:32:28.201
(METAL CLANGS)

1330
01:32:31.239 --> 01:32:33.008
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1331
01:32:49.730 --> 01:32:50.795
(JAKE GRUNTS)

1332
01:32:52.260 --> 01:32:53.831
(MAN YELLS)

1333
01:32:58.607 --> 01:33:00.218
Is that what you're looking for?

1334
01:33:00.301 --> 01:33:02.660
There she is
and she's not going...

1335
01:33:02.743 --> 01:33:03.808
(GROANS)

1336
01:33:05.042 --> 01:33:07.141
-(YELLS)
-(THUDDING)

1337
01:33:15.250 --> 01:33:16.755
-(DOOR SLAMS)
-(VOLKOV GRUNTS)

1338
01:33:20.189 --> 01:33:22.090
(PANTING)

1339
01:33:29.330 --> 01:33:31.099
(VOLKOV CHOKING)

1340
01:33:32.938 --> 01:33:34.758
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1341
01:33:34.841 --> 01:33:38.007
VOLKOV: Mona Lisa is mine!

1342
01:33:42.277 --> 01:33:43.617
(VOLKOV GRUNTS)

1343
01:33:49.757 --> 01:33:50.987
(YELLS IN PAIN)

1344
01:33:56.027 --> 01:33:57.862
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1345
01:33:58.898 --> 01:34:00.029
(LIGHTER CLICKS)

1346
01:34:03.133 --> 01:34:04.363
(WINCES)

1347
01:34:05.135 --> 01:34:06.838
(FIZZING)

1348
01:34:09.909 --> 01:34:11.289
(VOLKOV YELLS IN PAIN)

1349
01:34:11.372 --> 01:34:15.143
The Mona Lisa
is out of your league.

1350
01:34:16.212 --> 01:34:17.603
I'm not here for the bomb.

1351
01:34:17.686 --> 01:34:20.969
So what are you.
August's assassin?

1352
01:34:21.052 --> 01:34:23.382
No. I'm the distraction.

1353
01:34:33.064 --> 01:34:34.950
(ROCKS CRUMBLING)

1354
01:34:35.033 --> 01:34:36.362
Nice beard.

1355
01:34:40.071 --> 01:34:41.939
(STRAINS. GRUNTS)

1356
01:34:43.712 --> 01:34:45.290
(CRIES OUT IN PAIN)

1357
01:34:45.373 --> 01:34:47.010
Oh. fuck!

1358
01:34:54.250 --> 01:34:55.986
(GRUNTING)

1359
01:34:59.057 --> 01:35:01.189
Oh. Checkmate.

1360
01:35:08.297 --> 01:35:10.198
(DISTANT EXPLOSION)

1361
01:35:11.102 --> 01:35:12.266
Jake?

1362
01:35:14.974 --> 01:35:16.303
(SHOUTS) Jake?

1363
01:35:24.379 --> 01:35:26.280
(SOBBING)

1364
01:35:28.757 --> 01:35:30.449
(INHALES. SOBS)

1365
01:35:33.454 --> 01:35:35.894
-Jake!
-(EXPLOSION ECHOES)

1366
01:35:36.897 --> 01:35:38.292
(SOBS)

1367
01:35:39.900 --> 01:35:41.247
-Hey.
-(GASPS)

1368
01:35:41.330 --> 01:35:43.462
Jake! (LAUGHS)

1369
01:35:44.234 --> 01:35:45.922
-(GROANS)
-What's wrong?

1370
01:35:46.005 --> 01:35:48.155
-You okay?
-Yeah. No. I'm okay.

1371
01:35:48.238 --> 01:35:50.157
-Are you okay?
-I'm okay.

1372
01:35:50.240 --> 01:35:52.159
-(EXHALES)
-Hey. guess what?

1373
01:35:52.242 --> 01:35:53.747
What?

1374
01:35:55.245 --> 01:35:58.165
-I got this.
-Jake! (LAUGHS)

1375
01:35:58.248 --> 01:36:01.117
-(EXPLOSION)
-(DREA MOANS HAPPILY)

1376
01:36:15.265 --> 01:36:16.248
AUGUST: Jesus. Jake.

1377
01:36:16.331 --> 01:36:18.383
You look like you've been
chewed up. digested

1378
01:36:18.466 --> 01:36:20.286
and shit out by the War Machine.

1379
01:36:20.369 --> 01:36:23.025
Yeah. sounds about right.

1380
01:36:23.108 --> 01:36:25.174
Your fucking Mona Lisa's
at the bottom of a gorge.

1381
01:36:26.375 --> 01:36:27.799
I don't know what kind
of shape she's in

1382
01:36:27.882 --> 01:36:29.196
but she can't be detonated
without this.

1383
01:36:29.279 --> 01:36:31.198
Ah. damn.
Sounds like I gotta find me

1384
01:36:31.281 --> 01:36:33.937
a new Motherfucker
of Cultural Appropriation.

1385
01:36:34.020 --> 01:36:37.204
Or not. You could just
let it rest in peace.

1386
01:36:37.287 --> 01:36:38.975
Oh. no. no. Jake.

1387
01:36:39.058 --> 01:36:40.746
You're not naive enough
to believe

1388
01:36:40.829 --> 01:36:42.455
there are no more
Volkovs in the world.

1389
01:36:43.491 --> 01:36:45.113
No.

1390
01:36:45.196 --> 01:36:47.229
No. I just hope
you're not one of them.

1391
01:36:50.300 --> 01:36:53.070
Well. guess it's time for you
to sail away. Jake.

1392
01:37:00.508 --> 01:37:02.376
Enjoy your little boat.

1393
01:37:03.819 --> 01:37:06.050
I gotta build me
a kingdom to rule.

1394
01:37:15.094 --> 01:37:17.226
(SWEEPING MUSIC PLAYING)

1395
01:37:25.434 --> 01:37:27.533
(PROJECTOR WHIRRING)

1396
01:37:49.227 --> 01:37:51.095
(BOTTLES CLINK)

1397
01:38:05.144 --> 01:38:07.210
(SERENE MUSIC PLAYING)

1398
01:38:22.062 --> 01:38:24.128
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

1399
01:39:02.102 --> 01:39:03.662
(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

1400
01:39:37.698 --> 01:39:39.632
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

1401
01:41:01.089 --> 01:41:03.239
(MUSIC FADES)

1402
01:41:03.322 --> 01:41:05.388
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1403
01:44:24.754 --> 01:44:26.772
(MUSIC FADES)

1404
01:44:26.855 --> 01:44:29.427
(HEROIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1405
01:45:22.482 --> 01:45:23.482
(MUSIC FADES)
